cy. Model pruning removes redundant weights or attention heads, reducing model size and potentially accelerating inference, but requires careful calibration to avoid disproportionate accuracy loss, especially for generalist models. Holistically, these techniques are not mutually exclusive: production systems frequently combine quantization with continuous batching and PagedAttention for memory-efficient, high-throughput serving, while speculative decoding can be layered on top for latency-critical applications. The optimal configuration depends on deployment constraints — latency targets, available hardware, accuracy requirements, and request concurrency —

